## Key Equations/Formulas

```
Power of a Z-test:
  Step 1:  X̄* = μ₀ + z_α × (σ/√n)
  Step 2:  Z  = (X̄* − μ₁) / (σ/√n)
  Step 3:  β  = Φ(Z)
  Step 4:  Power = 1 − β

Sample size from margin of error:
  n = (z_{α/2} × σ / ME)²   → always round UP

In R (PWR package):
  pwr.t.test(n = 30, d = effect_size, sig.level = 0.05, alternative = "greater")
  # d = (μ₁ − μ₀) / σ
```

